result.name: 1988-1988-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-1988-eastern-irish-sea-gro
result.notes:
A series of groundfish surveys were carried out on fishing vessel Silver Star 
from 1976 to 1991 in the eastern Irish Sea. Fishing took place using a Boris 
Goshawk trawl towed for an hour. This data is from the 2 surveys carried out 
in 1988. Numbers at length by centimetre of the main commercial fish species 
are recorded. Station positions by area are recorded. A summary table is 
included for cruises 01/88 and 02/88 containing catch data for all other 
species.
